title: Kate Quarrie
text:
Kate Quarrie is a <a href="Canadians">Canadian</a> politician who served as the second female <a href="mayor">mayor</a> of <a href="Guelph">Guelph</a>, <a href="Ontario">Ontario</a> from 2003 to 2006.
A native of Guelph, Kate Quarrie was defeated by <a href="Karen%20Farbridge">Karen Farbridge</a> in the November 2006 municipal election.
